title: LISSANDRA
description: Lissandra is a powerful ice mage that freezes all in her path. She can be effectively played in both the mid and top lane. She has cost effective spells on a relatively short cooldown and her passive helps her harass early and often. With two forms of hard CC, she qualifies as perhaps the strongest mage in the game. As such, she is one of the most popular top laners in competitive play. Hauntzer recommends Lissandra because she has such a dominating presence.

title: ORIANNA
description: Orianna is a mage of a different sort. She stands alone as a League of Legends champion because each of her spells is based around her ball. She commands the ball to damage, slow, shock and shock her enemies, or speed up and protect her teammates. She excels in any situation in which she can buff her teammates. She is a fairly regular pick in competitive play. Slooshi recommends Orianna because she has high playmaking ability and thrives in teamfights.

title: KALISTA
description: Kalista is a highly mobile AD carry. Her strengths revolve around her ability to dash around any time she lands an auto attack. She stacks spear after spear into her enemies with each auto attack she lands, allowing her to chunk their health down. She is unique because she is one of the few champions that requires a teammate in order to use an ability. She is highly contested in competitive play because that ability happens to be one of the best engages in League of Legends. Doublelift recommends Kalista because she is super fun to play and you can crush your opposition.

title: XERATH
description: Xerath is a long range mage who struggles to control the the arcane energy surging through his body. He appears from time to time in competitive play, but can be a solo queue machine. His early game is good, his mid-game is better, but his late game is phenomenal. He has great wave clear and a passive that helps him stay in lane longer than most opposition. His ultimate allows him to greatly impact side lane trades without having to roam entirely to those lanes. AlexIch rates Xerath highly and recommends that players play him whenever they get the chance.

title: THRESH
description: Thresh is the soul-collecting ranged support that we all wish we could be. He plays like a melee champion but his auto attacks are ranged, which gives him a lot of lane pressure in the bottom lane. He is one of the top support picks in competitive play. With lots of CC in his kit and the ability to reposition his teammates to safety, he has the potential to create some of the most spectacular plays in the game. Thresh is BunnyFuFuu�s favorite champion. He recommends Thresh because he has low cooldowns later in the game and is a lot of fun to play.

title: VI
description: Vi is a jungle assassin that packs quite a punch. She clears the jungle with speed and is always a threat when ganking. Her kit allows for some of the best gap closing in the game and she combos well with just about every champion. She isn�t currently one of the most frequently picked junglers in competitive play, but has always made a strong showing when chosen. Saintvicious recommends Vi in every situation, whenever she isn�t banned.

title: CORKI
description: Corki is a mixed-damage AD carry. He has what might be considered the strongest early-game burst of all AD carries. This allows him to heavily bully opposing laners early-mid game. He has been a heavily contested pick in competitive play this season. Corki is a good pick for teams that find themselves heavy in physical damage or lacking magic damage. He can shred tanky targets that dive in his face or poke carries from range with his ult. He is a solid pick for almost any situation. As the most consistent AD carry in the 2015 LCS spring split, Cop recommends picking up Corki whenever you get the chance.

title: LEBLANC
description: Leblanc is one of the few mages remaining from a less honest time in Noxian history. She lives to deceive her enemies. One second she is here, the next, she isn�t. She uses her spells to close gaps and burst her opposition into oblivion. She thrives against most other mages, and can usually remove enemy carries completely from the fight. She is highly sought after in competitive play. Alex Ich recommends picking Leblanc whenever she is available.

title: JARVAN IV
description: Jarvan is a tough-as-nails jungler. He comes from a long line of royalty, and as such, he leads by example on and off the Rift. He clears the jungle effectively and his ganks can be devastating. In competitive play, he has been one of the most popular junglers. He can be played as a tank or an assassin depending on what his team needs. Saintvicious recommends Jarvan because of his high kill potential when ganking.

title: SIVIR
description: Sivir is a quick and ruthless AD carry, a master of the boomerang. She has good wave clear and excels at pushing lanes. She lacks an instant gap closer, but she makes up for it with prolonged speed boosts for her and her teammates. She has a spellshield that blocks the next spell that hits her. This makes her a formidable pick in lane because she is difficult to gank and can avoid enemy CC. She is one of the most frequently picked AD carries in the competitive scene. Cop recommends Sivir because she is reliable and has great chase potential with her ultimate.

title: MORGANA
description: Morgana is a protective mage support. She has both a strong engage and a strong disengage. She is one of the more heavily contested supports in competitive play. She can lock down enemies from the front line or sit back and protect her carries. She has a strong presence during the laning phase which discourages enemies from engaging on her ADC. During the mid and late game, her binding can lock down unsuspecting enemies from a very long distance, resulting in game-changing kills for her team. Bunny FuFuu holds Morgana in high esteem because of her pick potential.
